-- BMO Promotes Begy, Front Street Hires Brown: Vlaad
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-06-07T18:21:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-07/bmo-promotes-begy-front-street-hires-brown-vlaad-correct-.html
(Corrects headline to Begy promoted at  Bank of Montreal (BMO) 
and  Brian Porter  to CEO of Bank of Nova Scotia.)  Bank of Nova Scotia promoted Brian
Porter to chief executive officer from president as current CEO
Richard Waugh retires, according to Vlaad and Co., a Toronto-based financial services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:
* Ellen Costello, BMO Capital Markets U.S. country head is
retiring. Chief auditor Chris Begy will replace her.
* Front Street Capital Inc. hired Rick Brown as senior portfolio
manager of fixed income from Stanton Asset Management.
*  Uranium One Inc. (UUU)  hired Adam Schatzker as executive vice
president, strategy and business development. Adam was at RBC
Capital Markets as a director and research analyst.
* Shaez Allidina joined Deloitte & Touche Corporate Finance
Canada as a corporate finance analyst.
* PI Financial Corp. hired Amain Jain to its sales desk from
Raymond James Financial Inc. and Jose Estevez to the
institutional trading group from Desjardins Securities Inc.
* Mackie Research Capital added Adam Seanor as financial
services research analyst from M Partners.
*  Bank of Nova Scotia (BNS) ’s The WaterStreet Group Inc. hired Edwin
Wong as an investment counsellor from Mercer Investments.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
